author: Our World in Data
headline: Cases Data Source
snippet: COVID-19 cases dataset which is updated daily.

author: The Guardian
headline: UK Declines option to join EU scheme to source PPE
snippet: The UK government misses deadline to join the EU Scheme after being present at four meetings where it was discussed.

author: The Sunday Times
headline: Boris Johnson takes a working holiday
snippet: From the 14th to 24th of February, the UK prime minister takes a working holiday in Chevening.

author: ITV
headline: The UK Government announces 'herd immunity' strategy
snippet: The UK government announces it's strategy for dealing with COVID-19. This startegy requires 60% of the population to become infected.

author: BBC
headline: Boris Johnson decalres "business as usual"
snippet: The UK prime minister tells people to "wash their hands" but carry on with "business as usual." Within the next week he has attended a rugby union match with 82 000 others and 250 000 people attended the Cheltenham Festival.

author: The Telegraph
headline: COVID-19 patients are sent back to care homes
snippet: The UK Government tells hospitals to free up capacity by sending elderly people with COVID-19 to care homes.

author: The Telegraph
headline: The UK goes into lockdown
snippet: The UK enters lockdown much later than many European countries.

author: New Zealand TV
headline: Jacinda Ardern slams herd immunity
snippet: The New Zealand prime minister said that herd immunity was "never ever" an option for her country.

author: Radio New Zealand
headline: New Zealand charter a flight to evacuate it's citizens from Wuhan
snippet: New Zealanders are planned to be evacuated a day before the WHO declares COVID-19 a matter of "international concern".

author: Radio New Zealand
headline: New Zealand quarantines any foreign travellers passing through China.
snippet: New Zealand announces a 14-day quarentine is placed on foreign-nationals passing through China.

author: Radio New Zealand
headline: New Zealand closes borders
snippet: For the first time in their history, New Zealand close their borders.

author: Radio New Zealand
headline: The NZ government announces a 4 level alert system
snippet: New Zealand announces a 4 level alert system which they are on level 2 of (meaning social distancing is enforced).

author: Radio New Zealand
headline: NZ move to level 3 on their alert system
snippet: New Zealand reduces travel and begins to enter a lockdown state.

author: Radio New Zealand
headline: NZ move to level 4 on their alert system
snippet: 2 days after announcing level 3, New Zealand enters a full lockdown.

author: Wired
headline: Sweden officials say herd immunity has not gone as planned
snippet: Stockholm's population with antibodies is 7.3% while London's is 17%.

author: WHO
headline: WHO declares coronavirus an incident of "international concern"
snippet: After visiting China, the WHO declares coronavirus a "public health emergency of international concern".

author: BBC
headline: First COVID-19 death in Europe (France)
snippet: A Chinese tourist becomes the first person to die outside Asia from COVID-19.

headline: WHO Director General calls COVID-19 "public enemy number one"
snippet: Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus says "wake up and consider thisï¿½ virus as public enemy number one".

author: WHO
headline: WHO says "days make a difference"
snippet: The WHO publishes a report that states "days make a difference with a disease like this".

author: Radio New Zealand
headline: New cases outside China outnumbers those in China
snippet: For the first time, daily new cases outside of China outnumbers those in China.

headline: WHO declares COVID-19 a pandemic

author: WHO
headline: WHO urges governments to be pro-active
snippet: WHO tells governments to "find, isolate, test and treat" everyone with COVID-19.

author: WHO
headline: WHO tells governments to "test, test, test"

author: WHO
headline: WHO tells governments to track and trace
snippet: WHO says that "tracing every contact must be the backbone of the response in every country".
